Durban - A taxi driver who was gunned down at a service station in Phoenix on Thursday afternoon has died. According to KZN police spokesperson Captain Nqobile Gwala said a case of murder has been opened. "It is alleged that the taxi driver was at a petrol station at Aberdare Drive in Phoenix refueling his taxi when he was shot by unknown suspects. He sustained multiple gunshot wounds to the body. He was taken to a clinic where he later died. The motive for the attack is yet to be established," said Gwala. According to Prem Balram from Reaction Unit SA when medics arrived on scene they found the victim was found lying face down on the ground bleeding from multiple gun shot wounds to his body. Balram said witnesses reported seeing three men walking towards the victim before they fired multiple shots in his direction. He said atleast 9 cartridges were recovered at the scene. POST